# Neurex Git Commits

Commit policy for this repository. Format follows [Conventional Commits](https://www.conventionalcommits.org/en/v1.0.0/). Authoring guide: [git-commit-rules.mdc](git-commit-rules.mdc). Layout: [project-structure.mdc](project-structure.mdc).

```
<type>(<scope>): <description>

[optional body]

[optional footer]
```

Imperative mood, lowercase subject, no trailing period. Prefer ≤ 72 characters in the subject.

---

## Authorization

| Action | Allowed when |
|--------|----------------|
| `git commit` | User **explicitly** requests a commit (or user rules override) |
| `git push` | User **explicitly** requests push — do not offer push proactively |
| `git commit --amend` | User rules allow (unpushed HEAD, hook fixed files, user said amend) |
| `push --force`, `reset --hard`, etc. | User explicitly requests and understands impact |
| `git config` | Never |

If intent is unclear (“save this”, “finish up”), confirm whether to commit. Stage only paths for the current task unless the user approves a broader commit.

---

## Commit types

| Type | Use for |
|------|---------|
| `feat` | New component, CLI behavior, token layer, registry item |
| `fix` | Incorrect install, resolver, validation, or runtime behavior |
| `docs` | `docs/`, [AGENTS.md](../../AGENTS.md), package READMEs — no logic change |
| `test` | `packages/*/test/**` |
| `refactor` | Internal restructure, same intended behavior |
| `chore` | Tooling, deps, formatting, repo hygiene |
| `build` | `tsup`, turbo, generated artifact wiring |
| `ci` | CI workflows |
| `perf` | Measurable performance win |
| `style` | Formatting or class order only |

Use `docs` for documentation-only work, not `feat`.

---

## Scopes in this repository

pnpm workspace: `apps/*`, `packages/*` ([pnpm-workspace.yaml](../../pnpm-workspace.yaml)). Pick **one primary scope** per commit from where most lines changed (`git diff --stat`).

### Package scopes

| Scope | Paths |
|-------|--------|
| `tokens` | `packages/tokens/` |
| `ui` | `packages/ui/` |
| `registry` | `packages/registry/` (`src/`, `templates/`, `scripts/`) |
| `cli` | `packages/cli/` |
| `playground` | `apps/playground/` |

### Cross-cutting scopes

| Scope | Use when |
|-------|----------|
| `docs` | Multiple files under `docs/` or cross-package documentation |
| `repo` | Root `package.json`, `turbo.json`, `pnpm-workspace.yaml`, workspace scripts |
| `cursor` | `.cursor/rules/**` |
| `agents` | [AGENTS.md](../../AGENTS.md), `.agent/` (gitignored locally) |

Optional nested doc scopes when a single doc area dominates: `docs(tokens)`, `docs(cli)`, `docs(registry)`.

### Avoid as scope

- Component names (`button`, `dialog`) — put the name in the **description**: `feat(ui): add dialog component`
- `tests` — use `test(<package>)` e.g. `test(cli)`
- Vague scope on multi-package diffs — split commits or use `repo` with a body listing areas

### Multi-package workflow

Prefer separate commits:

```txt
feat(ui): add drawer component
feat(registry): add drawer item and sync templates
feat(tokens): add drawer component tokens
```

After `packages/ui` changes that affect install templates, run `pnpm registry:sync` before or note it in the `registry` commit body. After token generator changes, note `pnpm tokens:build` when registry style outputs depend on it.

